cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.CR, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on using micro-blogging services to crowdsource epidemics in real-time.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of social media for bio-surveillance and public health.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) could be a possible category as the paper may discuss the development of software tools for analyzing Twitter data.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) could be another possible category as the paper may discuss privacy and security concerns related to using social media for bio-surveillance.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) could also be a possible category as the paper may discuss the usability and effectiveness of using social media for public health surveillance.
